Data Cleaning¶

In [12]:
newCovid_Cases=newCovid_Cases.fillna(0)
newCovid_Cases["SS_ID"]=newCovid_Cases["SS_ID"].round(0).astype(int)
Location=Location.fillna(0)
Location["StateID"]=Location["StateID"].round(0).astype(int)

Table Schema Specification¶

In [13]:
CountrySchema = StructType([ StructField("CountryID", IntegerType(), True)\
                      ,StructField("CountryName", StringType(), True)])
newCovid_CasesSchema = StructType([ StructField("CC_ID", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("ConfirmedCases", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("Recovered", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("Deaths", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("Date", StringType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("LocationID", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("SS_ID", IntegerType(), True)])
School_open_statusSchema = StructType([ StructField("SS_ID", IntegerType(), True)\
                      ,StructField("SS_Name", StringType(), True)])
LocationSchema = StructType([ StructField("LocationID", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("Latitude", StringType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("Longitude", StringType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("StateID", IntegerType(), True)\
                       ,StructField("CountryID", StringType(), True)])	
StatesSchema = StructType([ StructField("StateID", IntegerType(), True)\
                      ,StructField("StateName", StringType(), True)])

Creating Spark dataframes from pandas dataframes¶

In [15]:
country_spark = spark.createDataFrame(country,schema=CountrySchema)
newCovid_Cases_spark = spark.createDataFrame(newCovid_Cases,schema=newCovid_CasesSchema)
School_open_status_spark = spark.createDataFrame(School_open_status,schema=School_open_statusSchema)
Location_spark = spark.createDataFrame(Location,schema=LocationSchema)
States_spark = spark.createDataFrame(States,schema=StatesSchema)

In [ ]:
country_spark.createOrReplaceTempView("country_spark_temp")
newCovid_Cases_spark.createOrReplaceTempView("newCovid_Cases_spark_temp")
School_open_status_spark.createOrReplaceTempView("School_open_status_spark_temp")
Location_spark.createOrReplaceTempView("Location_spark_temp")
States_spark.createOrReplaceTempView("States_spark_temp")

Total Confirmed Cases, Total Deaths, Total Recovered cases with all school Status for each Country¶

Through this Non Trivial Query we can see the trend of Following:¶

  • COVID Confirmed cases
  • Deaths Cases due to COVID
  • Recovered Cases from COVID #### For each country against each School Status as below
  • Academic break
  • Closed due to COVID-19
  • Fully open
  • Partially open ### Through that we can extract intuition that which school status effect the most for each country
In [ ]:
query="""
select * from 
(
  select  
  c.countryname as Country_Name,
  d.SS_Name as School_status,
  sum(a.confirmedcases) as Confirmed_Cases, --Total Confirmed COVID Cases
  sum(a.Deaths) as Deaths, --Total Deaths cases from Confirmed COVID Cases
  sum(a.recovered) as recovered --Total Recovered cases from Confirmed COVID Cases
  from newCovid_Cases_spark_temp a
  inner join Location_spark_temp b 
  on a.locationid=b.locationid
  inner join country_spark_temp c 
  on b.countryid=c.countryid
  inner join School_open_status_spark_temp d 
  on a.SS_ID=d.SS_ID 
  group by c.countryname,d.SS_Name 
)
result
order by country_name Asc
"""
result1=spark.sql(query)
result_pd=result1.toPandas()
result_pd.head(3)

Total Confirmed Cases, Deaths and recovered cases including all school status for each month.¶

Through this Non Trivial Query we can see the trend of Following:¶

  • COVID Confirmed cases
  • Deaths Cases due to COVID
  • Recovered Cases from COVID #### For three months April, May, June respectively against each School Status as below
  • Academic break
  • Closed due to COVID-19
  • Fully open
  • Partially open ### Through that we can extract intuition that which school status effect the most for each month
In [ ]:
query="""select * from (
select  
case 
when extract(months from date) == 4 then 'April'
when extract(months from date) == 5 then 'May'
when extract(months from date) == 6 then 'June' 
end Month,

d.SS_Name School_status,
sum(a.confirmedcases) Confirmed_Cases,
sum(a.Deaths) Deaths,
sum(a.recovered) recovered
from newCovid_Cases_spark_temp a
inner join Location_spark_temp b on a.locationid=b.locationid
inner join country_spark_temp c on b.countryid=c.countryid
inner join School_open_status_spark_temp d on a.SS_ID=d.SS_ID 
group by d.SS_Name,
case 
when extract(months from date) == 4 then 'April'
when extract(months from date) == 5 then 'May'
when extract(months from date) == 6 then 'June' 
end ) result
order by School_status asc,
case 
when month='April' then 1
when month='May' then 2
when month='June' then 3 end
"""
result2=spark.sql(query)
result_pd2=result2.toPandas()
result_pd2.head(3)

In [ ]:
query="""select * from (
select  
d.SS_Name School_status,
b.locationid,b.longitude,b.latitude,c.countryname,
sum(a.confirmedcases) Confirmed_Cases,
sum(a.Deaths) Deaths,
sum(a.recovered) recovered
from newCovid_Cases_spark_temp a
inner join Location_spark_temp b on a.locationid=b.locationid
inner join country_spark_temp c on b.countryid=c.countryid
inner join School_open_status_spark_temp d on a.SS_ID=d.SS_ID 
group by d.SS_Name,b.locationid,b.longitude,b.latitude,c.countryname
) result
order by locationid,longitude,latitude,countryname
"""
result3=spark.sql(query)
result_pd3=result3.toPandas()
result_pd3.head(3)

Plotting Total Confirmed Cases, Deaths and recovered cases for each location based on longitude and latitude¶

We can observe in the graphs that:¶
  • Mostly COVID Confirmed cases are mainly in South America and Asian region
  • Mostly COVID Deaths cases are mainly in South America
  • Mostly COVID Recovered cases are mainly in US, Europe and India.
